text.text:
A very beautiful temple situated right in the heart of the city.
The area is large enough to have gardens, multiple temples and a lot of space to walk and sit and spend some time. There are two huge grounds as well, apt for any large gathering such as katha and Ramleela manchan.
Regular upkeep is evident and a lot of effort has been put in to have everything that a temple should have. Must visit if you are in Bareilly.

Lots of snacks shops are also available to have breakfast, lunch, dinner after Darshan.

Few people would know that special architecture and design have been used to build their buildings.

text.text:
The most ancient temple of Nath Nagr, Bareilly as per the discussion I heard while passing by a meeting of old age people.üòÖ As per the beliefs no doubt, Baba Alakhnath ji fulfills everyone's wish if asked with pure heart. This Nath mandir is somewhat surrounded by forests, you can make this out while entering there. I have also seen some elephants and camels who were cared by Babas or ‡§Æ‡§π‡§Ç‡§§ when I used to visit there in my childhood in 2000s. Although now they have only horses, dogs and tortoise. The big statue of Hanuman ji is the first sight attraction of this temple followed by a road covered by trees that provide peace and coolness and it also have some benches. People used to come here for morning walk. During occasions this road is covered by vendors which gives a sight of "Mela". But while entering the Mandir's premises be careful about the slippery floor especially in rainy seasons as it accumulates algae all over and there can be chances of a slip so take hard steps while entering.
Rest everything is best.

text.text:
Shri Trivati Nath Temple is one of the six ancient temples dedicated to Lord Shiva. It is located on the outskirts of the city of Bareilly. Lord Shiva is also called Trivati Nath. According to legends, Lord Shiva or Trivati Nath prophesied that he would appear in the dream of a shepherd under the three banyan trees located in the dense forest in the panchal area.
It is widely believed by the devotees that whosoever worships Shri Tivati Nath with full faith and devotion gets all his desires fulfilled. The temple, therefore, draws huge crowds of devotees every day.

text.text: The best lord shiva temple in bareilly . You will get an opportunity to view its real beauty in mahashivratri festival . It has a small pond like structure and you will see all around fishes and ducks with a small mountain like structure on top of which lord shiva with maa parvati are present .
